.TH ctrlz 2m
.XI ctrlz - "File's termination style"
.SH NAME
ctrlz \- File's termination style
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ctrlz Mode"
.sp
\fBz\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
When enabled \fBctrlz\fR  indicates that an \s-1MS-DOS\s0 style '\fBctrl-z\fR'
file  termination  character  should be written out. When clear, a \s-1UNIX\s0
style of no termination character should be used.
.SH NOTES
This mode only effects the style in which the buffer is written if
.Ht auto 2m
mode is enabled.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
